South Korea Decrees
   New Ownership Limit
   On Provincial Banks
   ----
   Special to The Wall Street Journal
Under the new 15% limit, Lotte Group and Hyundai Group
will have to sell portions of their stakes in two provincial
banks within three years. Lotte and its subsidiaries own
25.5% of the Bank of Pusan, while Hyundai and its
subsidiaries hold 21.3% of the Kangwon Bank.
   Separately, the government said it plans to deregulate
retail oil prices completely, and allow new entrants in the
local oil-refining industry. Lee Won, director of the Energy
and Resources Ministry's Petroleum Policy Coordination
Division, also said the government plans to lift a restraint
on importing and exporting of some oil products such as
naphtha.